== How the Filter Values Work ==

Filters are simply created using bitwise OR (numbers are bit shifted first):

Example: 2 (Deathmatch) + 5 (Bomber Ball) = (1<<2) + (1<<5) = 4 + 32 = 36
 00000100 +
 00100000 =
 00100100 (binary) = 36 (decimal)